疫情中这6个字，影响着我们。
These six words in the epidemic affect us.
澎湃新闻。
The news is roaring.
澎湃新闻                      。
The news is roaring.
澎湃新闻。
The news is roaring.
有内涵的时政新媒体。
Connotation of the new political media.
澎湃新闻 龙慧当疫情过后，我们很可能会忘掉某些细节，但仍然会清晰的记得发生在今天的情绪和认识，可能会很快跟过去重新衔接起来。
When the epidemic is over, we will probably forget some details, but we will still remember clearly what happened in today's mood and understanding, and may soon reconnect with the past.
在这次疫情中有这六个字带给你我一种全新的认识和理解，影响我们这段时间的方方面面，这几个字或抽象，又具体。
These six words in this epidemic have brought you a new understanding and understanding that has influenced all aspects of our time, both abstract and specific.
①封：史无前例的封城，形成一个巨大的物理分割，城市、乡村、小区相互有机的切割，阻断人们的日常出行、物流。
The unprecedented closure of the city has created a huge physical division in which cities, villages and small areas cut each other organically, cutting off people's daily travel and logistics.
通过网络建立起的联系，同时又面对一种无形的虚拟封锁。
The connection that builds through network, at the same time face a kind of invisible fictitious blockade.
②困：我们被困于一个半封闭的空间，部分人开始远程网络办公、网络课堂，它们和生活已经混合一体。
"We are trapped in a semi-enclosed space, some people began remote network office, network classroom, they have been mixed with life."
③谣：在传播方式发生深刻改变的今天，社会进入了信息超载阶段，多种似是而非的传言在网络上获得了生存空间。
Ballad: Today, when the mode of communication has changed profoundly, the society has entered the stage of information overload. Many specious rumors have gained the living space on the network.
很难辨认哪个是可靠信息，哪个是谣言。
It is difficult to tell which is reliable and which is rumor.
④抢：口罩、消毒水、双黄连、蔬菜甚至还有卫生纸......是什么造成我们这样盲目的抢购？⑤罩：尽管日均口罩产量从年前的2000万只，到现在日产过亿。
Grab: Masks, disinfectant, doughnuts, vegetables and even toilet paper... What caused our blind panic buying? Blinds: Despite an average production of 20 million masks a day, we now produce more than 100 million masks a day.
按现在复工后需求量来计算，仍存在巨大缺口。
There is still a huge gap in terms of demand once work resumes.
⑥援：来自全国各地三四万人的医疗救治队伍、源源不断的医疗物资、生活物资运抵重灾区，是这次疫情得到快速有效控制的关键。
Assistance: The arrival of medical treatment teams, a steady flow of medical supplies and supplies from 30 to 40 thousand people from all over the country is the key to the rapid and effective control of the epidemic.
